eading crime in Canada.</p><p>Evans said a recent survey found people are more concerned about financial crime than any other.</p>"},{"type":"trustbar"},{"type":"articleRelated","display":"small-only"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"newsletterbox"}],"assetTags":["magnetic_stripe_card","fraud","law_crime","toronto","payment_systems","credit_card","credit_cards","point_of_sale_terminals"],"seoKeywords":"point-of-sale terminals,fraud,credit cards","promo":[],"paywallMode":"metered","storyuuid":"d0747fb1-0db0-49e3-92a7-28490c45c2f7","related":{"pubdays":0,"strategy":0},"seoHead":"Portable credit card terminals used in fraud","readtime":3,"headline":"Portable credit card terminals used in fraud","subheadline":"In what is the latest financial fraud, crooks are using distraction techniques to replace merchants&rsquo; machines with their own, police say.","breadcrumbs":[{"label":"News","relurl":"/news","url":"https://www.thestar.com/content/thestar/news.html"},{"label":"Crime","relurl":"/news/crime","url":"https://www.thestar.com/content/thestar/news/crime.html"}],"authors":[{"author":"Curtis Rush","credit":"Police Reporter"}],"liftigImage":{"captionPosition":"overlay","fullWindowMainart":false,"type":"image","imageid":"1203948","origImageSize":"1200x557","lastmodified":2700061000,"forceoriginal":false,"caption":"Police display the back of a point-of-sale terminal to show it has been tampered with.","source":"TORONTO STAR","credit":"CURTIS RUSH","url":"/content/dam/thestar/news/crime/2012/05/31/portable_credit_card_terminals_used_in_fraud/pointofsale.jpeg","renditions":[{"url":"https://images.thestar.com/Dmg9aJ2aSJ3u5dvhQnkOP61H4SI=/93x52/smart/filters:cb(2700061000)/https://www.thestar.com/content/dam/thestar/news/crime/2012/05/31/portable_credit_card_terminals_used_in_fraud/pointofsale.jpeg","width":93,"height":52,"scalefactor":8,"aspect":"wide"}]},"lastreplicated":"Thu., May 31, 2012","seopublisheddate":"2012-05-31","seomodifieddate":"","totalParas":20,"additionalEve